{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651759","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651759"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:27:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:27:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18491"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18491","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18491"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.02,0.85,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11220"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76763"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11220","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11220"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18491"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62256"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6977"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26043"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26273"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26325"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76763"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe sphincter of Oddi is an important anatomical structure in the regulation of digestive secretions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes its function?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Prevents reflux of bile into the gallbladder","Regulates blood flow to the pancreas","Controls gastric emptying","Controls release of bile and pancreatic secretions into the duodenum","Prevents reflux of duodenal contents into the stomach"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Econtrols release of bile and pancreatic secretions into the duodenum\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary function of the sphincter of Oddi (Image 1). This smooth muscle sphincter is located at the ampulla of Vater (Image 2) where the common bile duct and main pancreatic duct join before entering the duodenum. It regulates the flow of both bile and pancreatic enzymes into the duodenum during digestion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents reflux of bile into the gallbladder\u003C/strong\u003E - The direction of bile flow is controlled by pressure gradients and one-way valves in the biliary system\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegulates blood flow to the pancreas\u003C/strong\u003E - Blood flow to the pancreas is controlled by vascular smooth muscle, not the sphincter of Oddi\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EControls gastric emptying\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the function of the pyloric sphincter\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents reflux of duodenal contents into the stomach\u003C/strong\u003E - This is also a function of the pyloric sphincter\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe sphincter of Oddi relaxes in response to cholecystokinin, which is released when fatty foods enter the duodenum. This allows the coordinated release of bile and pancreatic enzymes for digestion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The sphincter of Oddi controls the flow of bile and pancreatic secretions into the duodenum.","The sphincter of Oddi is located at the ampulla of Vater where the common bile duct and main pancreatic duct join.","Cholecystokinin relaxes the sphincter of Oddi to allow bile and pancreatic secretions to enter the duodenum during digestion."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cBiliary system new\u201d by Vishnu2011 is under\u00a0Public Domain. \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Biliary_system_new.svg\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62256"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18491"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21399"},{"type":"media","id":"21420"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21399","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21399"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d7Ork5vXGeWlTXdQOutIdSJc3hmCi5.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d7Ork5vXGeWlTXdQOutIdSJc3hmCi5.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":597}},{"type":"media","id":"21420","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21420"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/CFOqLKz29REVrBSH53CHH9iUqeZame.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/CFOqLKz29REVrBSH53CHH9iUqeZame.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":508,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62256","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62256"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T09:25:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T09:26:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11220"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76763"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{